149 "§13A-6-126
150 (a) For purposes of determining jurisdiction of this
151 article, the offense is committed in this state if any of the
152 acts committed under Sections 13A-6-121, 13A-6-122, or
153 13A-6-123 either originate in or are received in this state.
154 (b) For purposes of determining jurisdiction of this
155 article, the offense is committed in any county in which any
156 part of the crime took place, the victim or defendant resided,
157 or any images were received.
158 (c) The purpose of this section is to confer
159 jurisdiction upon the courts of this state to the maximum
160 extent allowable under the Constitution of the United States
161 of America and the Constitution of Alabama of 19012022."
162 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
163 1, 2026.
